		<gotoAndStop label="start" />
		<text>Vertical black bars called <b>bar lines</b> divide the staff into <b>measures</b>.</text>
		<gotoAndPlay label="bar" />
		<text>The above staff has been split into two measures.</text>
		<gotoAndPlay label="timesig" />
		<text><b>Time signatures</b> define the amount and type of notes that each measure contains.</text>
	</section>
			
	<section>
		<gotoAndStop label="timesig2" />
		<text>In the above example, the first measure is in 4/4 time and the second measure is in 3/4 time.</text>
		<gotoAndPlay label="4/4" />
		<text>The first measure (4/4) contains four quarter notes.</text>
		<gotoAndPlay label="3/4" />
		<text>The second measure (3/4) contains three quarter notes.</text>
	</section>	

	<section>
		<gotoAndPlay label="timesig3" />
